P(tails)=\frac{13}{18}
P(tails|A) = \frac{1}{2}
P(A|tails) = P(tails|A)\frac{P(A)}{P(tails)} = \frac{3}{13}
P(B|tails) = P(tails|B)\frac{P(B)}{P(tails)} = \frac{4}{13}
P(C|tails) = P(tails|C)\frac{P(C)}{P(tails)} = \frac{6}{13}
\left(\frac{3}{13},\frac{4}{13},\frac{6}{13}\right)
P(tails|new\ priors) = \frac{1}{2}\cdot\frac{3}{13} + \frac{2}{3}\cdot\frac{4}{13} + 1\cdot\frac{6}{13} = \frac{61}{78}
