1
P(T|A) = 1/2, P(T|B) = 2/3,  P(T|C) = 1/1
P(A) = P(B) = P(C) = 1/3
P(TA) = P(T|A) P(A) = 1/6
P(TB) = P(T|B) P(B) = 2/9
P(TC) = P(T|C) P(C) = 1/3
P(TA \lor TB \lor TC) = P(TA) + P(TB) + P(TC) = 1/6 + 2/9 + 1/3 = 13/18
P(T(A \lor B \lor C)) = P(T) = 13/18
P(TA) / P(T) = P(A|T) = (1/6)/(13/18) = 3/13
P(TB) / P(T) = P(B|T) = (2/9)/(13/18) = 4/13
P(TC) / P(T) = P(C|T) = (1/3)/(13/18) = 6/13
